        <body rend="right">
            <div hand="#DL" n="DL">
                
<!-- Note: This fragment follows the coding practices of the Missionary Travels project, so that it can be integrated later on. AW -->
<!-- From Justin: "There are some symbols that are used as shorthand. An apostrophe is used for ‘the’ and a grave accent is used for ‘of’." -->

    <pb facs="liv_000102_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Missionary Travels, foot of p366-367, sh -->                
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="marginleft" hand="#U1" n="U1" rend="gray"><note>1 pp. 366-367</note></add><!-- the number '1' is within a circle, sh --> of the 5<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <persName ref="people.xml#pers0244">Cypriano</persName> <anchor xml:id="reorder-3"/> supplied  
<lb/>my men <metamark function="reorder" spanTo="#meta-10"/><seg corresp="#reorder-3">generously</seg><anchor xml:id="meta-10"/> with
<lb/><term type="plant_foodstuff">pumpkin</term>s and <term type="plant_foodstuff">maize</term>
<lb/>and then invited me to
<lb/>breakfast - which consisted
<lb/>of <term type="plant_foodstuff">earth nuts</term> and roasted
<lb/><term type="plant_foodstuff">maize</term> - Then boiled <term type="plant_foodstuff">manioc</term>
<lb/>roots and <term type="plant_foodstuff">earth nuts</term> - <add place="below">^</add> <subst><del type="cancelled">Then</del><add place="above">with</add></subst>
<lb/><term type="plant_foodstuff">guavas</term> and <term type="foodstuff">honey</term> as a
<lb/>desert - I felt sincerely
<lb/>grateful for this <del type="strikethrough" hand="#CL" n="CL">glorious</del> <add place="below">^</add> <add place="marginleft" hand="#CL" n="CL">magnificent</add>
<lb/>breakfast</p>
<lb/><p>At dinner <persName ref="people.xml#pers0244">Cypriano</persName> was
<lb/>equally <subst><del type="strikethrough" hand="#CL" n="CL">successful</del> <add place="marginleft" hand="#CL" n="CL">bountiful</add></subst> and
<lb/>several of his friends
<lb/>joined us <del type="strikethrough">at it in</del> doing
<lb/>justice to his hospitality
<lb/><metamark function="reorder" spanTo="#meta-11" resp="#CL" n="CL"/><seg corresp="#reorder-4">one of them cut up a
<lb/><term type="animal">fowl</term> with a knife &amp; fork</seg><anchor xml:id="meta-11"/>    
<lb/><del type="cancelled">and the others</del> <del type="cancelled" hand="#CL" n="CL">Then</del> <add place="marginleft" hand="#CL" n="CL"><metamark function="insertion"/>Before eating</add> all
<lb/>had water poured on
<lb/>the hands <add place="marginleft" hand="#CL" n="CL"><metamark function="insertion"/>by a female <orgName>slave</orgName></add> to wash them <supplied cert="high">-</supplied>
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="#CL" n="CL"><note><metamark function="transposition" ><choice><abbr>tr</abbr><expan>transpose</expan></choice></metamark></note></add><!-- this is an instruction to tranpose lines.JL --> <metamark function="insertion" resp="#CL" n="CL"/><anchor xml:id="reorder-4"/> Neither forks nor spoons
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="#CL" n="CL"><del type="strikethrough" hand="#DL" n="DL">however</del></add> were used <subst><del type="cancelled">for</del><add place="above">in</add></subst> eating
<lb/><del type="cancelled">but</del> <supplied cert="high">-</supplied> <choice><sic>the</sic><corr>The</corr></choice> repast was
<lb/>partaken of with decency
<lb/>and good manners
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="#U2" n="U2" rend="gray"><note>28</note></add> and concluded by washing
<lb/>the hands <del type="strikethrough">again</del> - as at first</p>             
<lb/><p>All of them could
<lb/>read and write with ease
<lb/>I examined <del type="cancelled">all</del> the books
<lb/>they possessed and found
<lb/>a small work on medicine</p>
      
    <pb facs="liv_000102_0002" n="0002"/> <!-- The writing on this page has bled through from liv_000102_0001, sh/>  -->
            </div>
            
        <div hand="#CL" n="CL">
    <pb facs="liv_000102_0003" n="0003"/> <!-- Missionary Travels, p454, sh --><!-- body of text by Charles Livingstone, sh --><!-- abbreviations used: ` for 'of', and ' for 'the', sh-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">nor varied <add place="marginleft" hand="#DL" n="DL"><metamark function="insertion"/>The <term type="animal"><placeName><country>Senegal</country></placeName> long claw</term> however maintains its place
    <lb/>and is the largest bird seen - We saw a <term type="animal">butcher bird</term>
    <lb/>in a trap as
    <lb/>we passed</add> <supplied cert="high">-</supplied>  <add place="below">There are</add> <choice><sic>Remarkably</sic><corr>remarkably</corr></choice> few small animals
<lb/>they having been hunted almost to extinction few
<lb/>insects except <term type="insect">ants</term> <choice><abbr>wh</abbr><expan>which</expan></choice> abound in considerable number
<lb/>and variety <supplied cert="high">-</supplied> <add place="marginleft" hand="#DL" n="DL"><metamark function="insertion"/>There are
    <lb/>scarcely any
    <lb/><term type="insect">common flies</term>
    <lb/>to be seen nor
    <lb/>are we ever <metamark function="query" rend="gray" resp="#U2" n="U2">?</metamark>
    <lb/>troubled by
    <lb/><term type="insect">mosquito</term>es <supplied cert="high">-</supplied></add> 
<metamark function="newParagraph">//</metamark> The air is still hot and oppressive <add place="marginleft" hand="#DL" n="DL"><metamark function="insertion"/>The intensely
    <lb/>bright sunlight
    <lb/>glances <w>peace<supplied>-</supplied>
    <lb break="no"/>fully</w> on the
    <lb/>evergreen
    <lb/>forest leaves
    <lb/>and all feel
    <lb/>glad when
    <lb/>the path
    <lb/>comes into
    <lb/>the shade</add> 
<lb/>The want of life in <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> scenery made me long to tread
<lb/>again <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> banks <choice><abbr>` '</abbr><expan>of the</expan></choice> <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0232"><choice><orig>Zambesi</orig><reg>Zambezi</reg></choice></geogName></placeName> and see <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> graceful <term type="animal">antelopes</term>
<lb/>feeding beside <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> dark <term type="animal">buffalo</term> and sleek <term type="animal">elands</term>
<lb/>Here <term type="animal">hippopotami</term> are known to exist only by <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice>
<lb/>footprints on <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> banks <space extent="3" unit="chars"/> No one is ever seen to blow
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="#U2" n="U2" rend="gray"><note>2 &amp; 3</note></add><!-- numbers within a circle, sh --> or put his head up at all <supplied cert="high">-</supplied> They have learned to
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="#U2" n="U2" rend="gray"><note>pp. 454-456</note></add> breathe in silence and <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">keep</add> out of sight <space extent="3" unit="chars"/> We never
<lb/>heard one uttering <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> snorting sound so common on the
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0232"><choice><orig>Zambesi</orig><reg>Zambezi</reg></choice></geogName></placeName> <space extent="4" unit="chars"/> We crossed two small streams
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="#DL" n="DL"><metamark function="insertion"/><del type="cancelled">Kangesi</del>
<lb/>the <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0107">Kanesi</geogName></placeName> &amp;
    <lb/><placeName><geogName type="river">Fombeji</geogName></placeName></add> 
    before reaching <placeName><settlement type="village" ref="settlement.xml#sett0030">Cabango</settlement></placeName> a village situated on <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice>
<lb/>banks of <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> <del type="strikethrough">river</del> <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0082">Chihombo</geogName></placeName> <space extent="5" unit="chars"/> The country
<lb/>was becoming more densely peopled as we <w>pro-
<lb break="no"/>ceded</w> but it bears no population compared to
<lb/>what it might easily sustain <supplied cert="high">-</supplied> <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>provisions
    <lb/>were to be had in great abundance a <term type="animal"><term type="foodstuff">fowl</term></term>
<lb/>and basket <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> <term type="foodstuff">meal</term> weighing 20<choice><abbr>lbs</abbr><expan>pounds</expan></choice> were sold for
<lb/>1 <choice><orig>½</orig><reg>1/2</reg></choice> <choice><abbr>yds</abbr><expan>yards</expan></choice> of very inferior cotton cloth worth not
<lb/>more than 3 pence <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>An idea <choice><abbr>` '</abbr><expan>of the</expan></choice> cheapness of
<lb/>food may be formed from <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> fact that <persName ref="people.xml#pers0450"><choice><abbr>Capt</abbr><expan>Captain</expan></choice>
<lb/>Neves</persName> purchased 380<choice><abbr>lbs</abbr><expan>pounds</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> <term type="plant">tobacco</term> from <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> <term type="tribe" ref="ethic-group.xml#ethnic0088">Bangalas</term>
<lb/>for about 2 pounds Sterling This when carried into
    <lb/><placeName><region ref="region.xml#region0038">Central Londa</region></placeName> might purchase seven thousand
    <lb/>five hundred <term type="animal"><term type="foodstuff">fowls</term></term> or feed with <term type="foodstuff">meal</term> &amp; <term type="animal"><term type="foodstuff">fowls</term></term>
    <lb/>seven thousand persons for one day giving each a <term type="animal"><term type="foodstuff">fowl</term></term>
<lb/>and 5 <choice><abbr>lbs</abbr><expan>pounds</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> <term type="foodstuff">meal</term> <space extent="5" unit="chars"/> When food is purchased
<lb/>here with either <term type="foodstuff">salt</term> or coarse calico 4 persons
<lb/>can be well fed with animal &amp; vegetable
<lb/>food at <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> rate <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> one penny a day - <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>The Chief
<lb/>vegetable food is <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> <term type="plant_foodstuff">manioc</term> and <term type="plant_foodstuff">lotsa meal</term></p>       
<lb/><p><del type="strikethrough">They</del> These contain a very large proportion <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> <term type="foodstuff">starch</term>

    <pb facs="liv_000102_0004" n="0004"/> <!-- The writing on this page has bled through from liv_000102_0003, sh/>  -->

    <pb facs="liv_000102_0005" n="0005"/><!-- body of text by Charles Livingstone. jl -->
<lb/>and when eaten alone for any length <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> time <w>pro-
<lb break="no"/>duce</w> most distressing <term type="ailment">heartburn</term> and as we ourselves
<lb/>experienced in coming north cause a weakness <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> vision
<lb/>as occurs in <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice>case <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> animals fed on pure gluten or
<lb/><choice><sic>amyllaceous</sic><corr>amylaceous</corr></choice> matter only - I now discovered that
<lb/>when these starchy substances are eaten along
<lb/>with a proportion of <term type="plant_foodstuff">earthnuts</term> <del type="cancelled">pu</del> <choice><abbr>wh</abbr><expan>which</expan></choice> <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">contain</add> <del type="strikethrough"><unclear cert="low">sweet</unclear>-oil</del>
<lb/><del type="strikethrough"><choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> <unclear cert="low">essence</unclear> is made</del> <add place="marginleft">a considerable 
    <lb/>quantity of oil</add> no injurious effects follow</p>               
<lb/><p>While on <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> way to <placeName><settlement type="village" ref="settlement.xml#sett0030">Cabango</settlement></placeName> we saw fresh tracks
<lb/><choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> <term type="animal">elands</term> the first we had <subst><del type="strikethrough">seen</del><add place="above">observed</add></subst> in this country <supplied cert="high">-</supplied>
<lb/>a poor little <orgName>slave</orgName> girl <del type="strikethrough">belonging to</del> being sick turned
<lb/>aside in <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> path and though we waited all <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> next day
<lb/>making search for her she was lost <del type="strikethrough">probably she</del> <supplied cert="high">-</supplied>
<lb/>she was tall and slender for her age as if of too quick
<lb/>growth and probably unable to bear <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> fatigue <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> the
<lb/>march lay down and slept in <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> forest then
<lb/>waking in <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> dark went farther and farther
<lb/>astray <space extent="3" unit="chars"/> The treatment <choice><abbr>` '</abbr><expan>of the</expan></choice> <orgName>slaves</orgName> when witnessed
<lb/>by my men certainly did not raise <term type="occupation">slaveholders</term>
<lb/>in their estimation Their usual exclamation
<lb/>was "<foreign xml:lang="und">Ga ba na pelu</foreign>" (They have no heart) and
<lb/>added in reference to <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> <orgName>slaves</orgName> "Why do they let them?"
<lb/>as if they thought that <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> <orgName>slaves</orgName> had <add place="below">^</add> <subst><del type="cancelled">a</del><add place="above"><choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice></add></subst> natural right to
<lb/>rid <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> world <choice><abbr>`</abbr><expan>of</expan></choice> such heartless creatures and ought
<lb/>to do it <space extent="7" unit="chars"/> The uneasiness <choice><abbr>` '</abbr><expan>of the</expan></choice> <term type="occupation">trader</term> <subst><del>is</del><add place="over-text">was</add></subst> continually
<lb/>showing itself and upon <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> whole he had reason to be
<lb/>on <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> alert both day &amp; night <space extent="3" unit="chars"/> the <term type="occupation">carriers</term> stole
<lb/>perpetually <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> goods entrusted to their care and
<lb/>he could not openly accuse them lest they
<lb/>might plunder him of all and leave him quite
<lb/>in the lurch - <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>he could only hope to manage
<lb/>them after getting all <choice><abbr>'</abbr><expan>the</expan></choice> remaining good<supplied cert="high">s</supplied> safely into
                    <lb/>a house in <placeName><settlement type="village" ref="settlement.xml#sett0030">Cabango</settlement></placeName> <space extent="3" unit="chars"/> then he might deduct
<lb/>something from their pay for what they had purloined</p></div>    
	    
